   The next day, I was the leader of the group at Orc 1.  Superbeing sent me a tell, asking if he  could join me.  I replied &quot;No, I grouped with you yesterday and you refused to cast any healing spells.&quot;  I expected him to argue, but he didn't.  He just said, &quot;Okay&quot;, as if we had heard that alot.  Mind Boggling.<br>
   Me, I do whack a mob from time to time, if mana permits.  Or if sitting will draw aggro in close quarters.  But I do know that first and foremost, it is my job to keep the party alive.  That's why they invited me, that is why I exist.  If someone dies in my group, I take it personally, even if all agree it was not my fault. <br>
     I am trying hard to learn the best way to do this without drawing aggro.  I am playing with my stun spells, learning when it is a good use of mana to cast them.  Teapray is the highest character I've ever had, and the only cleric I've played above 14.  I do make mistakes from time to time.  I am not the best cleric in Norrath, but I would like to be.  I've had group members tell me that I am good at what I do.  <br>
   I just wish there was a way to learn how to be a great cleric without making mistakes along the way.<br>
<br>
