<br>
I don't tell clerics what to use to heal me. Heck, I dont give out advice to anyone that is in my group.. they should know their class. Now if they are brand new to the area and ask for advice, I'll likely tell 'em what I know, and just as likely say &quot;Just do what you think is best.&quot;<br>
<br>
With a cleric healing, I do expect to be standing after the fight. (Unless everyone else is toast too.) If it's a one mob fight, why the heck did I just die? (with the cleric not saying OOM or otherwise warning me) ...that type of stuff gets me.  For this cleric..having been warned, well I wasnt' gonna give him much of a chance to kill me =P  He tried tho...  <br>
<br>
(To the person that said I'm a druid?  I'm a ranger... and was the main tank.)<br>
<br>
Good clerics... *HUGS*<br>
<br>
Bad clerics... *flees*<br>
<br>
To whoever says better not to have a cleric than a bad cleric... I TOTALLY agree.   But then again, i say that about EVERY class... better to have a great player behind a hybrid (the &quot;not so needed&quot; classes) then a bad player behind a &quot;core&quot; class, anyday.   And I gotta admit, except for the rez when things go bad, I prefer having a druid/shaman combo over a single cleric... then again, rez IS really nice :-)   Tho a cleric that uses stuns is a good thing.. but too many I guess got burned by folks telling them that it is a bad thing. In my personal opinion, I love stuns. I used to play a paladin and the thing I loved most was being able to chain cast stuns to keep a mob totally occupied while not taking any dmg. Sure I&quot;d run OOM quick as heck (maybe not now, this was before the increased mana pool for hybrids) but usually it was enough to survive a bad fight.<br>
<br>
And Jarkell.... you are 53. This was a 48 rogue.  How many hitpoints do you think he has, and does he warrant complete heal over the main tank (myself, 51 ranger, 2k hitpoints self buffed. With cleric buffs easily get 2500) ?  The rogue himself looked rather puzzled at that.... the cleric had almost killed him by casting too slow (the rogue was going down FAST when he was getting hit).<br>
<br>
